 </subsection>





<subsection><title>Exponential Rules</title>
  <p>
We saw several exponential rules in <xref ref="sec-exp-intro"/> and they were summarized in <xref ref="exp-rules"/>. 
We write the first three again here for easy reference, and this time we write them in terms of <m>e^x</m> because we will often need to use them in that format. 
  </p>

<assemblage xml:id="exp-rules-e"><title>Exponential Rules in terms of <m>e^x</m></title>
	<p>
		The following are true for all positive numbers <m>x</m> and <m>y</m>, and any real numbers <m>a</m> and <m>b</m>:
<men>e^xe^y=e^{x+y}</men>
<men>e^{x-y} = \frac{e^x}{e^y}</men>
<men>(e^x)^y = e^{xy}</men>
	</p>
</assemblage>
  </subsection>

