<exercise><title>Function Expression - HOMEMADE</title>
  <introduction>
      <image source="images/exp6" width="70%">
  </image>
    </introduction>
  <webwork>
    <pg-code>
      Context("Numeric");
        $radio = RadioButtons([
          'Function f',
          'Function g',
          'Function h',
          'Function P',
          'Function Q',
          'Function R',
        ],4);

      Context()->functions->disable('All');
      Context()->functions->enable('sqrt');
    </pg-code>

    <statement>
      <p>
        Which of the following could be the function in the graph above? 
<md> f(x)= 2 e^x </md>
<md> g(x)= e^x+3 </md>
<md> h(x)= 2 e^{-x} +3</md>
<md> P(x)= -3 e^{-x} +6 </md>
<md> Q(x)= \frac{1}{2} e^{-x} +3 </md>
<md> R(x)= \frac{1}{2} e^{x} +6 </md>
      </p>
      <p>
        Note: It is usually not possible to tell for sure what the expression of a function is just by looking at a graph. 
        However, it may be possibly to rule out several of the below functions, until there is only one option that is feasible. 
      </p>
        <p>
          <var name="$radio" form="buttons"/>
        </p>
    </statement>

  </webwork>
</exercise>

