<exercise><title>True or False? - HOMEMADE</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      (Not randomizable)
    </p>
  </introduction>
  <webwork>
    <pg-code>
      Context("Numeric");
$popup1 = PopUp(['?','True','False'],1);
$popup2 = PopUp(['?','True','False'],1);
$popup3 = PopUp(['?','True','False'],2);
$popup4 = PopUp(['?','True','False'],1);
$popup5 = PopUp(['?','True','False'],1);
$popup6 = PopUp(['?','True','False'],1);

      Context()->functions->disable('All');
      Context()->functions->enable('sqrt');
    </pg-code>

    <statement>
       <p>
Remember that <m>e</m> is a real number (a constant). 
You may see it most often as part of an exponential function such as <m>f(x)=e^x</m>, but <m>e</m> itslf is just a number. 

      
  Which of the following statements about the number <m>e</m> are true, and which are false? Try to answer all of them <alert>without using a calculator</alert>. 
      </p>
<p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        <m>2.5 \lt e \lt 3</m> <var name="$popup1" form="popup"/>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        <m>14 \lt 7e \lt 21</m> <var name="$popup2" form="popup"/>
      </p>
    </li>
        <li>
      <p>
        <m>(e^2)^3 = e^5</m>  <var name="$popup3" form="popup"/> 
      </p>
    </li>
        <li>
      <p>
        <m>0 \lt e^3 \lt 27</m>  <var name="$popup4" form="popup"/> 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        <m>e^a</m> is positive for all real numbers <m>a</m>  <var name="$popup5" form="popup"/> 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        <m>e^{-1} = \frac{1}{e}</m> <var name="$popup6" form="popup"/> 
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>
</p>
    </statement>
  </webwork>
</exercise>

<exercise><title>True or False? - HOMEMADE</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      (Not randomizable)
    </p>
  </introduction>
  <webwork>
    <pg-code>
      Context("Numeric");
$popup1 = PopUp(['?','True','False'],1);
$popup2 = PopUp(['?','True','False'],2);
$popup3 = PopUp(['?','True','False'],2);
$popup4 = PopUp(['?','True','False'],1);
$popup5 = PopUp(['?','True','False'],1);
$popup6 = PopUp(['?','True','False'],2);

      Context()->functions->disable('All');
      Context()->functions->enable('sqrt');
    </pg-code>

    <statement>
       <p>     
  Which of the following statements are true, and which are false? 
      </p>
<p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        If <m>x \lt y</m>  then <m>e^x \lt e^y</m> <var name="$popup1" form="popup"/>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        There is exactly one real number <m>x</m> such that <m>e^x = -1</m> <var name="$popup2" form="popup"/>
      </p>
    </li>
        <li>
      <p>
        <m>e^{x+y} = e^x+ e^y</m> for all numbers <m>x</m> and <m>y</m> <var name="$popup3" form="popup"/> 
      </p>
    </li>
        <li>
      <p>
        <m>\left(e^{x}\right)^y = \left(e^{y}\right)^x</m> for all numbers <m>x</m> and <m>y</m> <var name="$popup4" form="popup"/> 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        <m>e^{-2} = \frac{1}{e^2}</m>  <var name="$popup5" form="popup"/> 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        <m>e^{0} = 0</m> <var name="$popup6" form="popup"/> 
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>
</p>
    </statement>
  </webwork>
</exercise>


  </exercises>

